The Chemours Company, commonly referred to as Chemours, is an American chemical company that was founded in July 2015 as a spin-off from DuPont. It has its corporate headquarters in Wilmington, Delaware, United States.



Contents


1 History
2 Products
3 Corporate governance

3.1 Board of directors
3.2 Senior executives


4 References
5 External links



History[edit]
In October 2013, DuPont announced that it was planning to spin off its "performance chemicals" business into a new publicly traded company in mid-2015.[2] DuPont filed its initial Form 10 with the SEC in December 2014 and announced that the new company would be called "The Chemours Company".[3] The spin-off to DuPont shareholders was completed on July 1, 2015 and Chemours' stock began trading on the New York Stock Exchange on the same date.[4] Its 180,920,858 shares of common stock were distributed to DuPont shareholders at a par value of one cent each. Chemours has assumed various liabilities arising from lawsuits against DuPont encountered in the normal course of business.[5]
Products[edit]
Chemours manufactures and sells performance chemicals falling within three segments: Titanium Technologies (titanium dioxide); Fluoroproducts (refrigerants and industrial fluoropolymer resins and derivatives including Freon, Teflon and Viton); and Chemical Solutions (cyanide, sulfuric acid, aniline, methylamines, and reactive metals).
Corporate governance[edit]
Board of directors[edit]

Mark P. Vergnano
Curtis V. Anastasio
Bradley J. Bell
Richard H. Brown, Chairman of the Board
Mary B. Cranston
Curtis J. Crawford
Dawn L. Farrell
Stephen D. Newlin

Senior executives[edit]

Mark P. Vergnano, Chief Executive Officer[6]
Mark E. Newman, Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer[6]
E. Bryan Snell, President - Titanium Technologies[6]
Paul Kirsch, President - Fluoroproducts[6]
Christian W. Siemer, President - Chemical Solutions[6]
David C. Shelton, General Counsel and Corporate Secretary[6]
Beth Albright, Senior Vice President, Human Resources[6]
Erich Parker, Corporate Communications and Chief Brand Officer

